00:07:48.100 --> 00:07:49.669 line:5%,start
and maybe Abby could just

00:07:49.735 --> 00:07:51.137 line:95%,end
<i>let me be on the team.</i>

00:07:51.604 --> 00:07:53.573 line:95%,end
So you weren't in here for pyramid?

00:07:53.639 --> 00:07:55.007 line:95%,end
No. I was at the doctor's.

00:07:55.074 --> 00:07:56.542 line:95%,end
You don't know what--who's on top, what--

00:07:56.609 --> 00:07:58.478 line:95%,end
-what's going down this week?
-PAIGE: Uh-uh.

00:07:58.544 --> 00:08:00.446 line:95%,end
Me and Chloe were supposed
to have our duet.

00:08:00.513 --> 00:08:03.149 line:95%,end
So Abby told you, you had a duet this week

00:08:03.216 --> 00:08:04.484 line:95%,end
and now you can't dance it?

00:08:05.051 --> 00:08:07.553 line:95%,end
Aw. Did she tell you
who's going to be in it, instead?

00:08:07.620 --> 00:08:09.689 line:95%,end
She said that Chloe might be doing a solo.

00:08:09.755 --> 00:08:11.357 line:95%,end
Aw. That's all right.

00:08:11.424 --> 00:08:13.326 line:95%,end
There'll be other duets in your future.

00:08:13.793 --> 00:08:15.361 line:95%,end
<i>It happens all the time</i>

00:08:15.428 --> 00:08:16.996 line:95%,end
on dance teams,

00:08:17.063 --> 00:08:18.130 line:95%,end
<i>unfortunate for Paige,</i>

00:08:18.197 --> 00:08:19.899 line:95%,end
fortunate for Kendall.

00:08:19.966 --> 00:08:21.968 line:95%,end
KELLY: Hi, Paigey Mac!

00:08:22.034 --> 00:08:23.102 line:95%,end
HOLLY: Hello!

00:08:23.169 --> 00:08:24.003 line:95%,end
MELISSA: Hi, pumpkin.

00:08:24.070 --> 00:08:26.205 line:95%,end
-Did you learn anything in there?
-PAIGE: Uh-uh.

00:08:26.272 --> 00:08:27.607 line:95%,end
-HOLLY: You taking notes?
-What did you write in your book?

00:08:27.673 --> 00:08:28.674 line:95%,end
Nothing.

00:08:28.741 --> 00:08:29.976 line:95%,end
Jill's here.

00:08:30.042 --> 00:08:31.010 line:95%,end
KELLY: Oh what was she doing?

00:08:31.077 --> 00:08:32.879 line:95%,end
Asking questions about this weekend.

00:08:32.945 --> 00:08:35.114 line:95%,end
KELLY: <i>Why are she asking</i>
<i>what happened at pyramid?</i>

00:08:35.181 --> 00:08:36.883 line:95%,end
Like, Jill, you're not part of the group.

00:08:36.949 --> 00:08:37.950 line:95%,end
Get it through your head.

00:08:38.017 --> 00:08:39.185 line:95%,end
You're not part of our group.

00:08:39.252 --> 00:08:41.587 line:95%,end
It doesn't matter
what happened at pyramid.

00:08:41.654 --> 00:08:44.290 line:95%,end
(upbeat music playing)

00:08:45.791 --> 00:08:46.859 line:95%,end
Abby...

00:08:46.926 --> 00:08:48.461 line:95%,end
so Paige broke her foot?

00:08:48.528 --> 00:08:50.062 line:95%,end
Well, she didn't break her foot.

00:08:50.429 --> 00:08:52.899 line:95%,end
She broke her toe up into her foot.

00:08:53.366 --> 00:08:55.001 line:95%,end
I wish I could hear what was going on.

00:08:55.067 --> 00:08:55.902 line:95%,end
I know.

00:08:55.968 --> 00:08:57.270 line:95%,end
So what now with Paige out?

00:08:57.336 --> 00:08:59.438 line:95%,end
She told me she's out
for four to six weeks.

00:08:59.505 --> 00:09:01.107 line:95%,end
That has nothing to do with you.

00:09:01.173 --> 00:09:03.309 line:95%,end
Well, I understand not me, personally,

00:09:03.376 --> 00:09:04.877 line:95%,end
and that's very unfortunate.

00:09:04.944 --> 00:09:07.313 line:95%,end
But maybe now is there a spot for Kendall?

00:09:07.380 --> 00:09:09.215 line:95%,end
Oh, my God. She's like--

00:09:09.282 --> 00:09:10.783 line:95%,end
she can sniff out an opening.

00:09:10.850 --> 00:09:13.419 line:95%,end
She must have smelled Paige's
broken foot from a mile away.

00:09:13.486 --> 00:09:14.320 line:95%,end
She's like... (sniffs)

00:09:14.387 --> 00:09:16.322 line:95%,end
...there's a spot on the pyramid
for Kendall!

00:09:16.389 --> 00:09:17.990 line:95%,end
I'm the last person to ever

00:09:18.057 --> 00:09:19.892 line:95%,end
take Abby's side in anything.

00:09:19.959 --> 00:09:21.994 line:95%,end
But in the case of Jill versus Abby,

00:09:22.061 --> 00:09:23.129 line:95%,end
Abby wins.

00:09:23.195 --> 00:09:25.131 line:95%,end
Jill, you have to understand

00:09:25.197 --> 00:09:27.133 line:95%,end
that when you left

00:09:27.199 --> 00:09:28.734 line:95%,end
you didn't just disappear.

00:09:29.268 --> 00:09:31.637 line:95%,end
You went to this arch rival enemy.

00:09:31.704 --> 00:09:33.039 line:95%,end
Abby, we've been over this.

00:09:33.105 --> 00:09:36.208 line:95%,end
-I know.
-And it's very hurtful

00:09:36.275 --> 00:09:39.245 line:95%,end
and also just a slap in the face.

00:09:39.312 --> 00:09:40.646 line:95%,end
I was very hurt

00:09:40.713 --> 00:09:41.948 line:95%,end
by the way you treated Kendall.

00:09:42.014 --> 00:09:43.583 line:95%,end
-You can't be--
-You didn't let me do my job.

00:09:43.649 --> 00:09:44.850 line:95%,end
I want Kendall in the group.

00:09:44.917 --> 00:09:46.085 line:95%,end
I want Kendall in a duet.

00:09:46.152 --> 00:09:47.420 line:95%,end
<i>Really, lady?</i>

00:09:47.486 --> 00:09:49.755 line:95%,end
Did you not learn anything
the first time around?

00:09:49.822 --> 00:09:52.425 line:95%,end
You need to realize your place.

00:09:52.925 --> 00:09:54.594 line:95%,end
And you don't walk into a rehearsal.

00:09:54.660 --> 00:09:56.028 line:95%,end
You don't walk into pyramid.

00:09:56.095 --> 00:09:57.997 line:95%,end
You don't throw your kid at people.

00:09:58.064 --> 00:09:59.732 line:95%,end
I need to do what's best for Kendall.

00:09:59.799 --> 00:10:01.534 line:95%,end
I need to do what's best for the group.

00:10:01.601 --> 00:10:03.369 line:95%,end
-Don't you think Kendall deserves...
-You have to understand that.

00:10:03.436 --> 00:10:05.504 line:95%,end
-...to be in that group?
-Kendall deserves nothing.

00:10:05.571 --> 00:10:07.607 line:95%,end
-It's not like you're all entitled.
-JILL: Abby, do you want her to dance...

00:10:07.673 --> 00:10:09.175 line:95%,end
-ABBY: I want her to take class.
-JILL: ...dance here or not?

00:10:09.241 --> 00:10:10.443 line:95%,end
-ABBY: I want her to study.
-She's in class.

00:10:10.509 --> 00:10:12.445 line:95%,end
-ABBY: I want her to get better.
-She was in class last night, Abby.

00:10:12.511 --> 00:10:13.379 line:95%,end
ABBY: Uh-huh.

00:10:13.446 --> 00:10:15.448 line:95%,end
Let me tell you
who wasn't in class last night.

00:10:15.514 --> 00:10:17.116 line:95%,end
-Tell me.
-No Hyland kids.

00:10:18.184 --> 00:10:19.251 line:95%,end
No Chloe.

00:10:19.318 --> 00:10:20.453 line:95%,end
They don't come to class.

00:10:20.519 --> 00:10:21.887 line:95%,end
Kendall will come to class.

00:10:22.355 --> 00:10:24.090 line:95%,end
These moms who give me a hard time

00:10:24.156 --> 00:10:25.992 line:95%,end
for doing what's best for Kendall--

00:10:26.058 --> 00:10:27.760 line:95%,end
I know deep down inside

00:10:27.827 --> 00:10:29.629 line:95%,end
they would do the exact same thing.

00:10:29.695 --> 00:10:32.698 line:95%,end
I can't live with myself
that I took her away from here

00:10:32.765 --> 00:10:34.700 line:95%,end
and took that opportunity away from her.

00:10:34.767 --> 00:10:36.602 line:95%,end
So I really need you

00:10:36.669 --> 00:10:39.405 line:95%,end
and want you to give her another chance.

00:10:40.373 --> 00:10:42.742 line:95%,end
I'm sure she sees it
as a golden opportunity.

00:10:42.808 --> 00:10:45.344 line:95%,end
KELLY: <i>I went downstairs</i>
<i>because I heard Jill talking to Abby</i>

00:10:45.411 --> 00:10:46.479 line:95%,end
<i>at the front desk.</i>

00:10:46.545 --> 00:10:48.080 line:95%,end
<i>And I just wanted to let Jill know</i>

00:10:48.147 --> 00:10:49.548 line:95%,end
Paige is not out of the group.

00:10:49.615 --> 00:10:51.651 line:95%,end
She's injured and will be back.

00:10:51.717 --> 00:10:54.387 line:95%,end
So if she's trying to get Kendall
to replace Paige,

00:10:54.453 --> 00:10:55.655 line:95%,end
it's not happening.

00:10:55.721 --> 00:10:57.957 line:95%,end
Why did you ask Paige
who was replacing her in the duet?

00:10:58.024 --> 00:10:58.858 line:95%,end
I didn't.

00:10:58.924 --> 00:11:00.326 line:95%,end
KELLY: Why would go to Paige

00:11:00.393 --> 00:11:01.661 line:95%,end
and not the moms

00:11:01.727 --> 00:11:03.062 line:95%,end
about what's going on this weekend

00:11:03.129 --> 00:11:05.231 line:95%,end
before you put your claws in to get--

00:11:05.297 --> 00:11:06.532 line:95%,end
I didn't know Paige was in there.

00:11:06.599 --> 00:11:08.601 line:95%,end
-I didn't go scouting out Paige.
-But you didn't--

00:11:08.668 --> 00:11:10.002 line:95%,end
I went in. She was sitting there

00:11:10.069 --> 00:11:11.337 line:95%,end
-with a broken foot.
-But you didn't come up to Paige...

00:11:11.404 --> 00:11:12.838 line:95%,end
I said, "Honey, how are you?

00:11:12.905 --> 00:11:14.707 line:95%,end
-What happened?"
-...and say, so what's going this weekend?

00:11:14.774 --> 00:11:16.676 line:95%,end
JILL: I really didn't do anything
inappropriate.


00:11:20.780 --> 00:11:23.449 line:95%,end
(upbeat music playing)

00:11:25.651 --> 00:11:26.485 line:95%,end
ABBY: Hey, guys.

00:11:26.552 --> 00:11:28.421 line:95%,end
Maddie has to fly out tomorrow

00:11:28.487 --> 00:11:30.322 line:95%,end
morning to do <i>Drop Dead Diva.</i>

00:11:30.990 --> 00:11:32.391 line:95%,end
The group comes first.

00:11:32.458 --> 00:11:33.859 line:95%,end
Absolutely. I agree with you.

00:11:33.926 --> 00:11:35.161 line:95%,end
ABBY: <i>A couple of weeks ago,</i>

00:11:35.227 --> 00:11:37.897 line:5%,start
Maddie auditioned for a role
on <i>Drop Dead Diva.</i>

00:11:37.963 --> 00:11:40.566 line:95%,end
<i>She got the part,</i>
<i>and I'm thrilled for her.</i>

00:11:40.633 --> 00:11:42.835 line:95%,end
<i>But we have a competition this weekend.</i>

00:11:42.902 --> 00:11:45.004 line:95%,end
Missing a day of rehearsals is huge.

00:11:45.071 --> 00:11:47.373 line:95%,end
I don't want you to get out on stage
this weekend in competition,

00:11:47.440 --> 00:11:49.942 line:95%,end
and look like the yahoo
who doesn't know what they're doing.

00:11:50.443 --> 00:11:52.912 line:95%,end
This TV thing is a special event.

00:11:52.978 --> 00:11:55.548 line:95%,end
But I wish you were going to be here
tomorrow for rehearsal.

00:11:55.614 --> 00:11:57.983 line:95%,end
And that group dance better be perfect.

00:11:58.050 --> 00:11:59.418 line:95%,end
<i>When Maddie comes back,</i>

00:11:59.485 --> 00:12:01.253 line:95%,end
<i>she's going to have to play catch up.</i>

00:12:01.320 --> 00:12:04.156 line:95%,end
She better not come back
as some Hollywood diva.

00:12:04.223 --> 00:12:06.759 line:95%,end
(upbeat music playing)

00:12:06.826 --> 00:12:08.327 line:5%,start
And look,

00:12:08.794 --> 00:12:09.895 line:5%,start
hide it,

00:12:09.962 --> 00:12:11.297 line:5%,start
throw it.

00:12:11.363 --> 00:12:13.265 line:95%,end
It's all about the journal

00:12:13.332 --> 00:12:15.201 line:95%,end
and the diary of Anne Frank.

00:12:15.267 --> 00:12:17.136 line:95%,end
Brooke is doing a solo this week.

00:12:17.203 --> 00:12:18.871 line:5%,start
<i>It's about the Holocaust.</i>

00:12:18.938 --> 00:12:20.673 line:5%,start
I mean, this is serious for Brooke.

00:12:20.740 --> 00:12:23.442 line:95%,end
<i>I don't know if she has what it takes</i>
<i>to perform this number or not.</i>

00:12:23.509 --> 00:12:25.177 line:95%,end
(somber music playing)

00:12:25.244 --> 00:12:26.445 line:95%,end
Does anybody know anything

00:12:26.512 --> 00:12:28.114 line:95%,end
about this <i>Diary of Anne Frank?</i>

00:12:28.180 --> 00:12:29.882 line:95%,end
Because I have no clue of the story.

00:12:31.283 --> 00:12:34.053 line:5%,start
I can't believe that Kelly
doesn't know who Anne Frank is.

00:12:34.120 --> 00:12:37.089 line:95%,end
<i>I mean, that's a standard part</i>
<i>of curriculum in middle school.</i>

00:12:38.224 --> 00:12:39.992 line:95%,end
You didn't have to read
the <i>Diary of Anne Frank?</i>

00:12:40.059 --> 00:12:41.093 line:95%,end
-No.
-ABBY: Cartwheel.

00:12:43.162 --> 00:12:44.296 line:95%,end
Easy. Easy.

00:12:44.363 --> 00:12:45.931 line:95%,end
KELLY: <i>I don't really know much</i>
<i>about Anne Frank.</i>

00:12:45.998 --> 00:12:47.466 line:5%,start
But what I do know

00:12:47.533 --> 00:12:49.568 line:5%,start
is that I don't think
she was doing cartwheels.

00:12:50.970 --> 00:12:52.638 line:95%,end
There's a lot that goes into this piece.

00:12:52.705 --> 00:12:54.673 line:95%,end
And I'm watching Brooke,

00:12:54.740 --> 00:12:56.375 line:95%,end
<i>and she is just grimacing.</i>

00:12:56.442 --> 00:12:58.077 line:95%,end
Is she telling the story

00:12:58.144 --> 00:12:59.478 line:95%,end
or is she in pain?

00:12:59.545 --> 00:13:00.813 line:95%,end
KELLY: <i>I don't think Brooke should dance.</i>

00:13:01.147 --> 00:13:02.615 line:95%,end
<i>I took Brooke to a chiropractor</i>

00:13:02.681 --> 00:13:05.217 line:95%,end
<i>and he thinks that Brooke needs to rest.</i>

00:13:05.284 --> 00:13:06.585 line:95%,end
And I totally agree.

00:13:06.652 --> 00:13:09.155 line:95%,end
<i>Why can't brook do a dance</i>

00:13:09.221 --> 00:13:11.123 line:95%,end
with no acrobatics in her dance?

00:13:11.624 --> 00:13:12.958 line:95%,end
ABBY: You only have three days, kiddo,

00:13:13.025 --> 00:13:15.427 line:95%,end
before you are onstage doing this number.

00:13:15.494 --> 00:13:16.962 line:95%,end
You're dismissed for right now.

00:13:17.029 --> 00:13:17.897 line:95%,end
Go ahead and rest that,

00:13:17.963 --> 00:13:20.065 line:95%,end
and then I want you back in here
to finish it up.

00:13:23.469 --> 00:13:24.904 line:95%,end
<i>Can you start down here?</i>

00:13:25.204 --> 00:13:26.705 line:95%,end
MACKENZIE: <i>I'm rehearsing my solo today</i>

00:13:26.772 --> 00:13:28.307 line:5%,start
and it's a really fun dance.

00:13:28.374 --> 00:13:29.875 line:5%,start
And it's called <i>You Know You Love It.</i>

00:13:29.942 --> 00:13:31.343 line:5%,start
I know I love it.

00:13:31.410 --> 00:13:32.611 line:5%,start
(upbeat music playing)

00:13:32.678 --> 00:13:33.579 line:5%,start
