00:13:51.197 --> 00:13:54.133 line:95%,end
<i>I think she's really improving</i>
<i>as a dancer,</i>

00:13:54.200 --> 00:13:56.735 line:95%,end
as a performer and as an acrobat.

00:13:56.802 --> 00:13:58.771 line:95%,end
You need to get this choreography
in your head.

00:13:58.838 --> 00:14:00.639 line:95%,end
Go into the other room
and start working on it.

00:14:00.706 --> 00:14:02.141 line:95%,end
No tumbling!

00:14:03.909 --> 00:14:04.777 line:95%,end
Hi, guys.

00:14:05.244 --> 00:14:06.312 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: <i>Oh, God.</i>

00:14:06.378 --> 00:14:07.580 line:5%,start
Here comes Jill.

00:14:07.646 --> 00:14:09.215 line:5%,start
She and Kendall aren't even on the team.

00:14:09.281 --> 00:14:10.716 line:95%,end
<i>But we know Jill well enough to know</i>

00:14:10.783 --> 00:14:12.218 line:95%,end
that the absence of an invitation

00:14:12.284 --> 00:14:14.119 line:95%,end
isn't going to stop her from showing up.

00:14:14.186 --> 00:14:15.387 line:5%,start
-Hi, Kendall!
-Hey!

00:14:15.454 --> 00:14:18.791 line:5%,start
ABBY: So, Kendall,
I'm looking for a replacement

00:14:18.858 --> 00:14:20.759 line:95%,end
for the duet for Paige.

00:14:20.826 --> 00:14:22.895 line:95%,end
Abby's having auditions for the duet,

00:14:22.962 --> 00:14:24.897 line:95%,end
which I think is absolutely ridiculous

00:14:24.964 --> 00:14:27.199 line:95%,end
considering Kendall's not on the team.

00:14:27.266 --> 00:14:28.200 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: Kendall?


00:14:28.267 --> 00:14:29.869 line:95%,end
Oh, for the love of God.

00:14:30.970 --> 00:14:32.338 line:95%,end
Maddie is not auditioning

00:14:32.404 --> 00:14:34.506 line:95%,end
because she has solo this week.

00:14:34.573 --> 00:14:36.976 line:95%,end
Let's have Chloe and Nia do it.

00:14:38.143 --> 00:14:41.146 line:95%,end
(dramatic music playing)

00:14:46.585 --> 00:14:47.720 line:95%,end
ABBY: Nia...

00:14:47.786 --> 00:14:49.488 line:95%,end
some things are great.

00:14:49.555 --> 00:14:52.324 line:95%,end
I just think that you don't look
that great with her.

00:14:52.391 --> 00:14:53.525 line:95%,end
Like, it's a little off.

00:14:53.592 --> 00:14:54.426 line:95%,end
It's a little quirky.

00:14:54.493 --> 00:14:57.630 line:95%,end
You don't dance exactly the same.

00:14:57.696 --> 00:14:59.365 line:95%,end
You dance very much different.

00:15:00.766 --> 00:15:02.534 line:95%,end
-All right, let me see you and Kendall.
-Okay.

00:15:03.102 --> 00:15:03.936 line:95%,end
ABBY: And, one...

00:15:08.407 --> 00:15:09.308 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: I'm a little unclear.

00:15:09.375 --> 00:15:11.310 line:95%,end
Did Abby call you...

00:15:11.377 --> 00:15:12.478 line:95%,end
-JILL: No.
-...and say to come back?

00:15:12.544 --> 00:15:14.280 line:95%,end
No. She told me get--

00:15:14.346 --> 00:15:15.381 line:95%,end
get the kid in class.

00:15:15.447 --> 00:15:16.782 line:95%,end
So she's here, in class.

00:15:21.553 --> 00:15:22.922 line:95%,end
Do you think I went to Abby

00:15:22.988 --> 00:15:24.757 line:95%,end
and said put her in the duet?

00:15:24.823 --> 00:15:27.493 line:95%,end
If Abby does, it's because Abby
wanted her in there.

00:15:27.559 --> 00:15:28.394 line:95%,end
Why couldn't you say,

00:15:28.460 --> 00:15:30.896 line:95%,end
"Wow, what a nice thing for Kendall
if she's selected?"

00:15:30.963 --> 00:15:32.164 line:95%,end
I don't think it's fair for her

00:15:32.231 --> 00:15:34.767 line:95%,end
